abstract: Body believed to be the remains of a male homeowner is discovered in Northern California house destroyed by wildfire, bringing death toll from destructive fires to six.
lead_paragraph: A body was found in a burned-out home in Northern California, bringing the death toll to six from two of the state’s more destructive wildfires in recent memory, the authorities said Wednesday.

headline.main: California: Wildfire Deaths Rise to Six
